<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/878> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #878" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "With the Dictator Poetelius, according to Livy (9.28.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/873> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #873" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 9.26.7; Fast. Cap.; Degrassi 36f., 110, 418f.; cf. Diod. 19.76.3 ({Gr})." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/855> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #855" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 9.20.1 (with cognomina Flaccina and Venox); Diod. 19.2.1 ({Gr}); Fast. Cap. (names entire, with cognomina Flaccinator and Venno); Chr. 354 (Venno et Flaccina{155}tore); Fast. Hyd. (Venoce et Flaccino); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 36f., 109, 416f. Plautius subdued Teanum Apulum and Canusia in Apulia (Liv. 9.20.4-6; cf. Diod. 19.10.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/842> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #842" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (M. Fos[lius C. f. M. n. Flac]cinator Ma[g- -]). See Degrassi 36f., 109, 416f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/839> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #839" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The various names of Consuls, Dictators, and Masters of Horse, are filled out from Fast. Cap. and Act. Tr., Papirius from Fast. Cap. on 315, Publilius, ib. on 315, Maenius and Folius, ib. 314, and Manlius, Act. Tr. on 340. See Degrassi 36f., 68f. On the surrender of persons to the Samnites, see also Cic. Off. 3.109; Sen. 41; Gell. 17.21.36; Flor. 1.16.11; Dio fr. 36.19-21, and Zon. 7.26. On Papirius, see also 326, note 1, and 319, Consuls." .
